Subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC659FFA9B8A8F8DFB503F8CA" authority="Chamberlin, 1919" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[708,1085,1807,1833]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pelogeniinae">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC659FFA9B8A8F8DFB25CF8CA" bold="true" box="[708,866,1807,1833]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Pelogeniinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C659FFA9B905F8DFB503F8CA" author="Chamberlin R. V." box="[873,1085,1807,1833]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 514" refId="ref28995" refString="Chamberlin R. V. 1919. The Annelida Polychaeta of the Albatross Tropical Pacific Expedition, 1891 - 1905. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard 31: 1 - 514. Available from http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / bibliography / 49195  / summary [accessed 24 Feb. 2022]." type="journal article" year="1919">Chamberlin, 1919</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3786552C659FFA8BA8FF883B3B7FCEE" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C659FFA9BA8FF883B06BF88E" blockId="6.[227,341,1875,1901]" box="[227,341,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading id="D09581B5C659FFA9BA8FF883B06BF88E" bold="true" box="[227,341,1875,1901]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC659FFA9BA8FF883B06BF88E" bold="true" box="[227,341,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C659FFA9BA8FF853B4A3F7ED" blockId="6.[224,1437,1923,2063]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C659FFA9BA8FF853B0D8F87D" author="Claparede E." box="[227,486,1923,1950]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="313 - 584" refId="ref29056" refString="Claparede E. 1868. Les Annelides chetopodes du Golfe de Naples. Memoires de la societe de Physique et d'Histoire naturelle de Geneve 19 (2): 313 - 584." type="journal article" year="1868">Claparède (1868: 415)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the tribe-group Polylepides to refer to worms with elytra on all segments. 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC659FFA9BA8CF879B367F820" authority="Claparede, 1868" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1868" box="[224,601,1961,1987]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Lepidopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC659FFA9BA8CF879B0B7F820" box="[224,393,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Lepidopleurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C659FFA9BBFAF879B367F820" author="Claparede E." box="[406,601,1961,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="313 - 584" refId="ref29056" refString="Claparede E. 1868. Les Annelides chetopodes du Golfe de Naples. Memoires de la societe de Physique et d'Histoire naturelle de Geneve 19 (2): 313 - 584." type="journal article" year="1868">Claparède, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was the genus originally proposed for these worms, but it is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC659FFA9BBEAF81EB3FDF80B" authority="Risso, 1826" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[390,707,1998,2024]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Lepidopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC659FFA9BBEAF81EB311F80B" box="[390,559,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Lepidopleurus</emphasis>
Risso, 1826
</taxonomicName>
(Mollusca, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC659FFA9B93FF81EB52EF80A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[851,1040,1998,2025]" class="Polyplacophora" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="class">Polyplacophora</taxonomicName>
), as a consequence 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C659FFA9BE90F81EB4A3F80A" author="Grube A. E." box="[1276,1437,1998,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref29367" refString="Grube A. E. 1878. Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, Series 7 (25, 8): 1 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 85345" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube (1878)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC659FFA9BB35F824B0F8F7ED" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[345,454,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC659FFA9BB35F824B0F8F7ED" box="[345,454,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Polylepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Earlier, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C659FFA9B855F824B232F7ED" author="Grube A. E." box="[569,780,2036,2062]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="46 - 72" refId="ref29334" refString="Grube A. E. 1876. Bemerkungen uber die familie der Aphroditen (Gruppe Polynoina, Acoetea, Polylepidea). Schlesische Gesellschaft fur vaterlandische Cultur 53: 46 - 72." type="journal article" year="1876">Grube (1876: 72)</bibRefCitation>
examined topotype Naples specimens and recognized
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C658FFA8BA8FFEFFB3B7FCEE" blockId="7.[226,1438,303,781]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BA8FFEFFB0B2FEAA" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[227,396,303,329]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Lepidopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BA8FFEFFB0B2FEAA" box="[227,396,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lepidopleurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, noting an alternation of elytra and “branchiae” (he also referred to them as cirri) in the specimens. Two years later, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8B832FE88B212FE90" author="Grube A. E." box="[606,812,344,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref29367" refString="Grube A. E. 1878. Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, Series 7 (25, 8): 1 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 85345" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube (1878: 16)</bibRefCitation>
proposed an alternative name for worms with elytra on all segments, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BBDDFE51B380FE78" authority="Grube, 1878" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[433,702,385,411]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BBDDFE51B320FE78" box="[433,542,385,411]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Polylepis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8B84AFE51B380FE78" author="Grube A. E." box="[550,702,385,411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref29367" refString="Grube A. E. 1878. Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, Series 7 (25, 8): 1 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 85345" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however, he doubted the steady elytral pattern of the genus. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8BA89FE7AB0F4FE27" author="Chamberlin R. V." box="[229,458,426,452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 514" refId="ref28995" refString="Chamberlin R. V. 1919. The Annelida Polychaeta of the Albatross Tropical Pacific Expedition, 1891 - 1905. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard 31: 1 - 514. Available from http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / bibliography / 49195  / summary [accessed 24 Feb. 2022]." type="journal article" year="1919">Chamberlin (1919)</bibRefCitation>
proposed Polylepidae based on 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8B932FE7AB54EFE27" authority="Grube, 1878" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[862,1136,426,452]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8B932FE7AB2F5FE27" box="[862,971,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Polylepis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8B9B4FE7AB54EFE27" author="Grube A. E." box="[984,1136,426,452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref29367" refString="Grube A. E. 1878. Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, Series 7 (25, 8): 1 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 85345" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and included 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BF49FE7AB096FE0E" authority="Schmarda, 1861" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Pelogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BF49FE7AB4A2FE27" box="[1317,1436,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pelogenia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8BA8FFE03B096FE0E" author="Schmarda L. K." box="[227,424,467,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref30547" refString="Schmarda L. K. 1861. Neue wirbellose Thiere beobachtet und gesammelt auf einer Reise um die Erde 1853 bis 1857. Turbellarien, Rotatorien und Anneliden, Leipzig 1: 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1861">Schmarda, 1861</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, diagnosing this family by having elytra on all segments. However, he noticed the conflict within the two genera and the diagnosis of the family group and concluded that, if 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BF43FE2CB4A2FDF5" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[1327,1436,508,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BF43FE2CB4A2FDF5" box="[1327,1436,508,534]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Polylepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a valid genus, it would belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8B8F4FDF5B210FDDC" authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1856" box="[664,814,549,575]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Sigalionidae</taxonomicName>
, and that the name of his proposed group Polylepidae would have to be changed to Pelogeniidae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8B887FD9EB2D3FD8A" author="Chamberlin R. V." box="[747,1005,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 514" refId="ref28995" refString="Chamberlin R. V. 1919. The Annelida Polychaeta of the Albatross Tropical Pacific Expedition, 1891 - 1905. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard 31: 1 - 514. Available from http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / bibliography / 49195  / summary [accessed 24 Feb. 2022]." type="journal article" year="1919">Chamberlin 1919: 92</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8BE68FD9FB5C3FD8A" author="Hartman O." box="[1028,1277,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref29631" refString="Hartman O. 1959. Catalogue of the Polychaetous Annelids of the World. Allan Hancock Foundation" type="book" year="1959">Hartman (1959: 117)</bibRefCitation>
clarified that there are no species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BB90FDA8B359FD71" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[508,615,632,658]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BB90FDA8B359FD71" box="[508,615,632,658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Polylepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that it should be regarded as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BF66FDA8B0B2FD5F" authority="Kinberg, 1856" authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1856" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BF66FDA8B4A0FD71" box="[1290,1438,632,658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Psammolyce</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8BA8FFD71B0B2FD5F" author="Kinberg J. G. H." box="[227,396,673,700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="381 - 388" refId="ref29940" refString="Kinberg J. G. H. 1856. Nya slagten och arter af Annelider. Ofversight of Koniglich Vetenskapsakademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm 12: 381 - 388." type="journal article" year="1856">Kinberg, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8B874FD71B3B1FD58" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[536,655,673,699]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Pelogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8B874FD71B3B1FD58" box="[536,655,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pelogenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8B8A4FD71B24FFD58" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1826" box="[712,881,673,699]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Lepidopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8B8A4FD71B24FFD58" box="[712,881,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lepidopleurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C658FFA8B98CFD71B59BFD58" author="Pettibone M. H." box="[992,1189,673,699]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref30430" refString="Pettibone M. H. 1997. Revision of the sigalionid species (Polychaeta) referred to Psammolyce Kinberg, 1856, Pelogenia Schmarda, 1861, and belonging to the subfamily Pelogeniinae Chamberlin, 1919. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 581: 1 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.581" type="journal article" year="1997">Pettibone (1997)</bibRefCitation>
revised 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC658FFA8BF64FD71B4A2FD58" authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1856" box="[1288,1436,673,699]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC658FFA8BF64FD71B4A2FD58" box="[1288,1436,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Psammolyce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and reinstated 
